Long-term memory pointer ledger

Purpose:
- Pointer ledger for durable memory locations and external setup references.

Verification status: current-state memory; verify with the `.uai` audit before relying on it.
Memory scope: mid-to-long-term memory routing, documentation pointers, and UAIX MATM setup anchors.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains route URLs only, no credentials.
Update route: use https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit for authenticated MATM memory updates; update this local pointer ledger when durable routes change.
Source of truth: live MemoryEndpoints.com public evidence routes, repository docs, and `.uai/totem.uai`.
Next action for agents: use hosted MATM when reachable and authenticated, but keep local `.uai` active always.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, or raw one-time keys.

